# 🌿 EnviroScan — AI-Powered Pollution Source Identifier

An end-to-end machine learning pipeline that classifies pollution sources 
across 165+ Indian districts using 232,000+ real-time environmental records.

## 🔍 Overview
EnviroScan integrates data from CPCB, OpenWeather, and OpenStreetMap APIs 
to identify and classify pollution sources with 92.20% test accuracy using 
XGBoost — helping authorities pinpoint industrial, vehicular, and natural 
pollution contributors at scale.

## ✨ Features
- Real-time data ingestion from 3 public APIs
- 13 domain-specific engineered features (pollutant levels, meteorological 
  data, spatial proximity)
- SMOTE class balancing for imbalanced pollution categories
- Model comparison: XGBoost vs Random Forest vs Decision Tree
- Hyperparameter tuning via RandomizedSearchCV

## 🛠️ Tech Stack
`Python` `XGBoost` `Scikit-learn` `Pandas` `NumPy` `SMOTE` `OpenWeather API` `CPCB API`

## 📊 Results
| Model | Test Accuracy |
|-------|-------------|
| XGBoost | **92.20%** |
| Random Forest | 89.4% |
| Decision Tree | 84.1% |

